.\" Man page for pcap-parser(1)
.\" Generated 2026-05-16 — Sprint 12 Distribution & Ship Readiness
.TH PCAP\-PARSER 1 "May 2026" "pcap-parser 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pcap\-parser \- network capture analyzer — extract devices, conversations, and structured reports from PCAP/PCAPNG files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pcap\-parser
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIPCAP_FILE\fR
.br
.B pcap\-parser
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIDIRECTORY\fR
.br
.B pcap\-parser
\fB\-\-regression\fR
.br
.B pcap\-parser
\fB\-\-download\-instructions\fR
.br
.B pcap\-parser
\fIbefore.pcap\fR \fIafter.pcap\fR \fB\-\-compare\fR
.br
.B python \-m pcap_parser
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIPCAP_FILE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pcap\-parser
reads PCAP or PCAPNG capture files and produces structured reports including:
.IP \(bu 4
Device inventory: MAC addresses, vendor names (IEEE OUI), IP addresses, TCP/UDP ports, packet counts.
.IP \(bu 4
Conversation analysis: bidirectional flow tracking, byte/packet counts, TCP flag detection,
application protocol inference, and connection status classification.
.IP \(bu 4
Advanced analysis (Sprint 10): device role inference, network segmentation, topology graphs,
traffic anomaly detection, and timeline visualization.
.PP
Output formats include CSV, JSON (D3-visualization-ready), and streaming newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON).
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Basic Options"
.TP
\fBPCAP_FILE\fR
Path to a .pcap or .pcapng file, or a directory containing capture files.
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fINAME\fR
Output base filename (default: derived from pcap file name).
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR
Directory for generated reports (default: \fBoutputs\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fIFMT\fR
Output format: \fBcsv\fR, \fBjson\fR, or \fBboth\fR (default: \fBboth\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable verbose per-packet debug logging.
.SS "Streaming Output"
.TP
\fB\-\-stream\-json\fR, \fB\-\-stream\-ndjson\fR
Write newline-delimited JSON (NDJSON) records to stdout instead of files.
Each line is a self-contained JSON object with a \fBtype\fR field:
\fBdevice\fR, \fBconversation\fR, or \fBsummary\fR.
Useful for piping into \fBjq\fR, \fBduckdb\fR, or other streaming consumers.
.SS "Filtering & Comparison"
.TP
\fB\-\-filter\fR \fIEXPR\fR
Wireshark/tshark display filter expression (e.g. \(aq\fBtcp.port==443\fR\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-compare\fR
Diff two captures: \fBpcap\-parser before.pcap after.pcap \-\-compare\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-stats\-only\fR
Print summary statistics only \(em no output files written.
.SS "Validation & Regression"
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-output\fR
Validate generated output files against JSON Schema contracts.
.TP
\fB\-\-regression\fR
Run the committed golden regression suite and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-regression\-manifest\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to regression fixture manifest (default: \fBfixtures/regression_manifest.json\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-regression\-actual\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR
Directory with regenerated outputs to compare against golden fixtures.
.SS "Performance"
.TP
\fB\-\-benchmark\fR
Profile parsing and write a performance benchmark report.
.TP
\fB\-\-benchmark\-output\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path for benchmark JSON output (default: \fBoutputs/<base>\-benchmark.json\fR).
.SS "Advanced Analysis (Sprint 10)"
.TP
\fB\-\-analyze\fR
Run all advanced analysis: roles, segments, topology, anomalies, timeline.
.TP
\fB\-\-summary\fR
Print executive summary report after parsing.
.TP
\fB\-\-roles\fR
Print inferred device roles (router, server, workstation, IoT, etc.).
.TP
\fB\-\-anomalies\fR
Detect and print traffic anomalies.
.TP
\fB\-\-timeline\fR
Print conversation activity timeline.
.TP
\fB\-\-analysis\-json\fR \fIPATH\fR
Write full analysis results to JSON file.
.TP
\fB\-\-geoip\-db\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to MaxMind GeoLite2-City.mmdb for GeoIP enrichment.
.TP
\fB\-\-analysis\-bucket\fR \fISEC\fR
Timeline bucket size in seconds (default: 60).
.SS "Time Slicing"
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-start\fR \fITS\fR
Slice: start time (unix timestamp).
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-end\fR \fITS\fR
Slice: end time (unix timestamp).
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-src\fR \fIIP\fR
Slice: source IP filter.
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-dst\fR \fIIP\fR
Slice: destination IP filter.
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-proto\fR \fIPROTO\fR
Slice: protocol filter (TCP, UDP).
.TP
\fB\-\-slice\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR
Slice: port filter.
.SS "Other"
.TP
\fB\-\-download\-instructions\fR
Show instructions for downloading the IEEE OUI database.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Parse a single capture and write CSV+JSON reports:
.RS
pcap\-parser capture.pcapng
.RE
.TP
Stream NDJSON output for pipeline processing:
.RS
pcap\-parser large.pcap \-\-stream\-json | jq \(aqselect(.type == "device")\(aq
.RE
.TP
Process all PCAPs in a directory:
.RS
pcap\-parser ./captures/ \-\-output myaudit
.RE
.TP
Quick statistics without writing files:
.RS
pcap\-parser large_capture.pcap \-\-stats\-only
.RE
.TP
Filter packets to TCP port 443 only:
.RS
pcap\-parser capture.pcap \-\-filter "tcp.port==443"
.RE
.TP
Diff two captures:
.RS
pcap\-parser before.pcap after.pcap \-\-compare
.RE
.TP
Profile performance:
.RS
pcap\-parser capture.pcapng \-\-benchmark
.RE
.TP
Advanced analysis with GeoIP:
.RS
pcap\-parser capture.pcapng \-\-analyze \-\-geoip\-db GeoLite2\-City.mmdb
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I oui.txt
IEEE OUI database (MAC prefix to vendor mapping). Download from
https://standards-oui.ieee.org/oui/oui.txt
.TP
.I oui.csv
Cached OUI database in CSV format (auto-generated from oui.txt).
.TP
.I outputs/
Default output directory for reports.
.TP
.I schemas/v1.0.0/
JSON Schema contracts for output validation.
.TP
.I fixtures/regression_manifest.json
Golden regression fixture manifest.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OUTPUT_DIR
Override the default output directory (equivalent to \fB\-\-output\-dir\fR).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Error (missing tshark, validation failure, regression failure, streaming failure).
.SH LIBRARY USAGE
The package can be imported as a Python module:
.PP
.RS 4
from pcap_parser import parse_capture, parse_capture_streaming
.PP
# One-shot parse
.br
data = parse_capture("capture.pcapng")
.br
print(data.devices, data.conversations)
.PP
# Streaming
.br
for record in parse_capture_streaming("capture.pcapng"):
.br
    print(json.dumps(record))
.RE
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.IP \(bu 4
Python 3.10+
.IP \(bu 4
tshark (Wireshark CLI) \(em required for packet parsing
.IP \(bu 4
PyShark (Python wrapper for tshark)
.IP \(bu 4
jsonschema (optional, for output validation)
